Rotor Experiment Class 1 - Obstacle Trial 19
This is a trial with only an ablated obstacle no RP or CV changed and no ectopic trigger

This is a gradient of ablations. 
It is in the general shape of of a rectangle. 
The lightest ablations are closest to the beat node with the ablations getting 
denser as the gradient goes towards the back of the sheet. 
There are still pathways left open for the wave to travel, 
but the gradient slows down the wave much like fibrosis in a normal heart.
